<p align="center"><font size="7">Installation</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">The face alive features are fully integrated into 
the newest version of the virtual classroom Student Tool. To install the Student 
Tool just follow the directions specified in the Readme file of the Student Tool 
directory(also shown below).</font></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">Sun Java SDK Installation<br>
----------------------------------<br>
* Please make sure a Java SDK, or JRE are installed before running<br>
the Student Tool.<br>
* Follow the directions at Sun's website for installing the Java software.<br>
* Make sure to set your path correctly!<br>
<br>
Starting Java Student Tool<br>
----------------------------------<br>
* Make sure to run the Java Student from the directory that contains<br>
the images directory, library directory, and the files config_student.ini <br>
and config_facealive.ini.<br>
* The file config_student.ini specifies the name server. For example the<br>
host for Pitt is adam.cs.pitt.edu and the port number is 2020. The file<br>
config_facealivep.ini specifies the image server. For example the host <br>
for Pitt is adam.cs.pitt.edu and the port number is 7654.<br>
* Double click StudentTool410.jar to begin the program, or from the<br>
command line from inside the Java Student Tool V4 directory type <br>
java -jar StudentTool410.jar</font></p>

